---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout 
  title="Dental Fillings" 
  category="Restorative Dentistry"
  description="Fix cavities with various filling materials including composite, porcelain, and silver amalgam. Restore your teeth's health and function."
  image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1606811841689-23dfddce3e95?w=1920&h=600&fit=crop"
>
  
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-100 to-accent-200/50 border-l-4 border-accent-300 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-2">Cavity Treatment & Restoration</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-0">
        Dental fillings fix cavities by removing decay and filling the space with various materials 
        including composite, porcelain, and silver amalgam. We'll help you choose the best option 
        based on the location, size, and your personal preferences.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Understanding Dental Cavities
    </h2>
    
    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
        Cavities are permanently damaged areas in teeth that develop into tiny holes. They're caused by bacteria 
        in your mouth that produce acid, which gradually dissolves tooth enamel. If left untreated, cavities 
        grow larger and deeper, potentially leading to infection, pain, and tooth loss.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 rounded-full mx-auto mb-3 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl">ü¶∑</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Early Stage</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">White spots appear as enamel begins to weaken</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-orange-100 rounded-full mx-auto mb-3 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Cavity Formation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Holes form in enamel, may reach dentin layer</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 rounded-full mx-auto mb-3 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-2xl">üî¥</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Advanced Decay</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Reaches pulp, causing pain and potential infection</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Types of Dental Fillings
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-8 mb-12">
      <!-- Composite Fillings -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-primary-100/30 rounded-xl p-8">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Composite (Tooth-Colored) Fillings</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              Made from a mixture of resin and fine glass particles, composite fillings can be precisely 
              matched to your tooth color for a natural appearance.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Advantages:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Natural appearance</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Bonds directly to tooth</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Mercury-free</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Less tooth removal needed</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Can be repaired if damaged</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-orange-700 mb-2">Considerations:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>‚Ä¢ May stain over time</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Not as durable as amalgam</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Higher cost</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Takes longer to place</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-primary-100 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Front teeth, visible areas, small to medium cavities
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
            <div class="w-64 h-48 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-24 h-24 text-primary-900" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M14.828 14.828a4 4 0 01-5.656 0M9 10h.01M15 10h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Amalgam Fillings -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-50 to-gray-100/30 rounded-xl p-8">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center order-2 md:order-1">
            <div class="w-64 h-48 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-24 h-24 text-gray-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-4">Silver Amalgam Fillings</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A durable mixture of silver, tin, copper, and mercury that has been used safely 
              in dentistry for over 150 years.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Advantages:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Extremely durable</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Less expensive</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Quick to place</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Proven track record</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Ideal for back teeth</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-orange-700 mb-2">Considerations:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Metallic appearance</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ May cause tooth discoloration</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Expands/contracts with temperature</li>
                  <li>‚Ä¢ Contains mercury</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Back teeth, large cavities, patients on a budget
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Porcelain Fillings -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-50 to-accent-100/30 rounded-xl p-8">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-4">Porcelain Inlays & Onlays</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              Custom-made ceramic restorations created in a lab for superior fit, durability, 
              and aesthetics. Sometimes called "indirect fillings."
            </p>
            
            <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                <span><strong>Inlays:</strong> Fit within the tooth cusps (like traditional fillings)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                <span><strong>Onlays:</strong> Cover one or more cusps or the entire biting surface</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-accent-100 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Large cavities, fractured teeth, replacing old fillings
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
            <div class="w-64 h-48 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-24 h-24 text-primary-900" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M11.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.519 4.674a1 1 0 00.95.69h4.915c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-3.976 2.888a1 1 0 00-.363 1.118l1.518 4.674c.3.922-.755 1.688-1.538 1.118l-3.976-2.888a1 1 0 00-1.176 0l-3.976 2.888c-.783.57-1.838-.197-1.538-1.118l1.518-4.674a1 1 0 00-.363-1.118l-3.976-2.888c-.784-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h4.914a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.519-4.674z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      The Filling Procedure
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 to-primary-100/30 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary-900 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">1</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Numbing</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            Local anesthetic ensures you're comfortable throughout the procedure
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary-900 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">2</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Decay Removal</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            We carefully remove all decayed tooth material using specialized instruments
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary-900 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">3</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Filling Placement</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            The chosen filling material is carefully placed and shaped
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary-900 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-xl">4</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Final Adjustments</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            We shape and polish the filling to ensure proper bite and comfort
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Choosing the Right Filling Material
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
        The best filling material depends on several factors. We'll help you make an informed decision 
        based on your specific situation.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Factors to Consider:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              </div>
              <span><strong>Location:</strong> Visible areas favor tooth-colored options</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              </div>
              <span><strong>Size:</strong> Larger cavities may need more durable materials</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              </div>
              <span><strong>Chewing forces:</strong> Back teeth need stronger materials</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              </div>
              <span><strong>Budget:</strong> Different materials have different costs</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-900 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <span class="text-white text-xs font-bold">‚Ä¢</span>
              </div>
              <span><strong>Allergies:</strong> Some patients prefer metal-free options</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Our Recommendation Process:</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="font-bold text-primary-900">1.</span>
              <span>Thorough examination and diagnosis</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="font-bold text-primary-900">2.</span>
              <span>Discussion of all suitable options</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="font-bold text-primary-900">3.</span>
              <span>Explanation of benefits and limitations</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="font-bold text-primary-900">4.</span>
              <span>Cost comparison and insurance coverage</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="font-bold text-primary-900">5.</span>
              <span>Your final decision based on informed choice</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-semibold text-dental-charcoal mb-6">
      Caring for Your Fillings
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Immediate Care (First 24 Hours)</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-yellow-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Avoid chewing on the treated side until numbness wears off</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-yellow-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Some sensitivity to hot/cold is normal</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-yellow-500 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Stick to soft foods initially</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Long-Term Care</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Brush and floss regularly</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Regular dental checkups every 6 months</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Avoid biting hard objects (ice, pencils, etc.)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-300 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            <span>Report any sensitivity or discomfort</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-semibold mb-4">
        Don't Let Cavities Get Worse
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Early treatment of cavities prevents more extensive procedures later. If you're experiencing 
        tooth sensitivity or suspect you have a cavity, schedule an appointment as soon as possible.
      </p>
      <a href="#book-appointment" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent-300 text-primary-900 px-6 py-3 rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-accent-200 transition-colors">
        Schedule Your Filling Appointment
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Related Services -->
  <div slot="related-services" class="space-y-3">
    <a href="/services/dental-restoration" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">Dental Restoration</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Comprehensive restoration services</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/services/crowns-bridges" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">Crowns & Bridges</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">For extensive damage</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/services/general-dentistry" class="block p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-dental-charcoal">General Dentistry</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Complete dental care</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div slot="faq" class="space-y-6">
    <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer">How long do dental fillings last?</summary>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Composite fillings typically last 5-7 years, while amalgam fillings can last 10-15 years or more. 
        Longevity depends on the size of the filling, location in the mouth, your oral hygiene, and 
        eating habits. Regular checkups help monitor filling condition.
      </p>
    </details>
    
    <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer">Are amalgam fillings safe?</summary>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Yes, amalgam fillings have been used safely for over 150 years. The mercury in amalgam combines 
        with other metals to form a stable compound. Major health organizations including the ADA and FDA 
        confirm their safety. However, we offer mercury-free alternatives if preferred.
      </p>
    </details>
    
    <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer">Will getting a filling hurt?</summary>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        We use local anesthetic to ensure you're comfortable during the procedure. You may feel slight 
        pressure but should not experience pain. Some sensitivity is normal for a few days after the 
        procedure but typically resolves quickly.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-lg cursor-pointer">Can fillings be replaced?</summary>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Yes, fillings can be replaced when they wear out, crack, or leak. We regularly check your fillings 
        during routine visits and will recommend replacement when necessary. You can also choose to 
        replace amalgam fillings with tooth-colored options for aesthetic reasons.
